    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Traumatic or non-progressive vascular SCI

          -  Less than 45 days after lesion

          -  Any neurological level

          -  Complete and incomplete lesions

          -  If patient has been treated with glucocorticoids, it should have passed at least 7
             days from the end of the treatment

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Cauda equina syndrome

          -  Autoimmune disorder

          -  Tumor (even if benign)

          -  Neurodegenerative disease
      </textblock>
